    <article>
      <h2 class="diary-title title is-size-2" id="11-mans-search-for-meaning">
        <a href="#11-mans-search-for-meaning">Man&rsquo;s Search for Meaning, Viktor Frankl</a>
      </h2>

      <section class="content">
        <blockquote>
          <p>The greatest task for any person is to find meaning in his or her life.</p>

          <p>Emotion, which is suffering, ceases to be suffering as soon as we form a clear and precise picture of it.</p>

          <p>There is nothing in the world, I venture to say, that would so effectively help one to survive even the worst conditions as the knowledge that there is a meaning to one&rsquo;s life.</p>

          <p>What matters, therefore, is not the meaning of life in general but rather the specific meaning of a person&rsquo;s life at a given moment.</p>

          <p>The more one forgets himself &mdash; by giving himself to a cause to serve or another person to love &mdash; the more human he is and the more he actualizes himself.</p>

          <p>For the world is in a bad state, but everything will become still worse unless each of us does his best.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

